-lab2.cpp
-CMakeLists.txt

Open a terminal in the directory and do the following operation:
1) cmake .
2) make all
3) ./Lab2 data/checkerboard_images data/test_image.png

The program uses 2 command line arguments (argv[1] and argv[2]) to get:
-argv[1]: Path of the folder containing the images regarding the checkerboard ( data/checkerboard_images )
-argv[2]: Path of the test image (data/test_image.png)

If there will not be 2 command line arguments there will be considered the following paths as default:
../data/checkerboard_images/*.png 
../data/test_image.png


I used CLion on Linux Mint to write the code for this homework.
